The S. I. A. I (Savoia) S. 9 was an Italian flying boat, manufactured in 1918 by Societa Idrovolanti Alta Italia, and as a reconnaissance aircraft was used. Allegedly, French engineers are to be involved in the development of been. A crash series caused a negative popularity of the aircraft.
GeschichteDie wing bracing was unusual for a einstie leagues double-Decker. At the point of intersection of the bracing wires was inserted strut between the wings, an additional Auxiliary, so that the appearance of a two-handled double was deckers. The boat-shaped hull was made of wood, the wings were covered with fabric and were reinforced leading edges. The drive consisted of a Fiat A-12bis engine with 300 HP, a two blade propeller drive. The S. 9, of the S. 8, a 7.7 mm MG, as well as the possibility of a 50-kg bombs under the wings to carry. S. 9 grew out of the experiences with the p. 8, however, the success of the machine. Two p. 9 delivered have been lost already during the ferry flight. The pilots were killed in the crash. The error was a poorly glued Propeller, the disassembled during the flight into its components; in this context, it was the talk of Sabotage. The S. 9 was manufactured in France under the name of CAMS C-9 in license.
